<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1622,2035]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,341,1661,1687]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific name 
<taxonomicName box="[569,686,1661,1686]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudophasmatidae" genus="Decidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phasmida" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnifica">
<emphasis box="[569,686,1661,1686]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">magnifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(lat. = magnificent) refers to the strikingly beautiful colouration of the live 
<number box="[277,321,1699,1725]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="33.0">33</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[337,465,1699,1726]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 10" captionStartId="13.[151,271,1676,1700]" captionTargetBox="[313,1273,387,1651]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[313,1273,387,1652]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 10: Live 3 Decidia magnifica n. sp. photo taken at Piedras Blancas, Santa Elena, Medellín, Antioquia showing the beautiful colouration of this species (© Y. Rosas)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/187443/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Figs. 
<number box="[403,465,1699,1726]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="9.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="9.0">
9 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[418,433,1699,1725]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">–</emphasis>
10
</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1622,2035]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,331,1738,1764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Closely related to the type-species 
<taxonomicName authority="Westwood, 1859" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1859" box="[769,1136,1738,1764]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudophasmatidae" genus="Decidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phasmida" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="soranus">
<emphasis box="[769,903,1739,1764]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">D. soranus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Westwood" box="[920,1127,1738,1764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="51" refString="Westwood, J. O. (1859) Catalogue of Orthopterous insects in the collection of the British Museum. Part 1: Phasmidae. British Museum, London, 196 pp., 40 plates." type="book" year="1859">
Westwood, 
<number box="[1065,1127,1738,1764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="1859.0">1859</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
with which it shares the presence of tegmina and alae. It however differs by: the very pretty colouration (e.g. green body, orange antennae, blue head, bright red tegmina and costal region of the alae); less distinct ocelli and shorter alae of both sexes, which at best reach to abdominal tergite V (Ƥ) or VI (
<number box="[947,991,1854,1880]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="33.0">33</number>
). 
<number box="[1016,1060,1854,1880]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="33.0">33</number>
furthermore differ by: the more strongly deflexed and almost hemispherical lateral surfaces, lack of a median tooth on the lateral margin and much shorter posteromedian projections of the anal segment (
<figureCitation box="[887,975,1932,1958]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="14.[151,269,1791,1815]" captionTargetBox="[171,1396,188,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[171,1415,103,1863]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19: Genitalia of Decidia spp. [scale = 1 mm]. 11. D. blapoides (Redtenbacher, 1906), 3 (MNHN), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 12. D. blapoides (Redtenbacher, 1906), Ƥ HT (MNCN), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 13. D. doylei (Caudell, 1906), 3 (MNCN), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 14. D. doylei (Caudell, 1906), Ƥ (MNCN), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 15. D. magnifica n. sp., 3 HT (MEFLG), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 16. D. magnifica n. sp., Ƥ PT (MEFLG), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 17. D. soranus (Westwood, 1859), 3 (ANSP), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 18. D. magnifica n. sp., 3 HT (MEFLG), left cercus (caudal view). 19. D. doylei (Caudell, 1906), 3 (MNCN), anal segment and cerci (caudal view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/187444/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[943,975,1932,1958]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
), as well as the apically more rounded cerci (
<figureCitation box="[225,313,1970,1996]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="14.[151,269,1791,1815]" captionTargetBox="[171,1396,188,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[171,1415,103,1863]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19: Genitalia of Decidia spp. [scale = 1 mm]. 11. D. blapoides (Redtenbacher, 1906), 3 (MNHN), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 12. D. blapoides (Redtenbacher, 1906), Ƥ HT (MNCN), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 13. D. doylei (Caudell, 1906), 3 (MNCN), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 14. D. doylei (Caudell, 1906), Ƥ (MNCN), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 15. D. magnifica n. sp., 3 HT (MEFLG), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 16. D. magnifica n. sp., Ƥ PT (MEFLG), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 17. D. soranus (Westwood, 1859), 3 (ANSP), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 18. D. magnifica n. sp., 3 HT (MEFLG), left cercus (caudal view). 19. D. doylei (Caudell, 1906), 3 (MNCN), anal segment and cerci (caudal view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/187444/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[281,313,1970,1996]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ƥ may also be distinguished by the presence of rounded posterolateral lobes on abdominal tergites VII 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[284,299,2008,2034]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">–</emphasis>
IX and shorter subgenital plate, which hardly reaches half way along anal segment (
<figureCitation box="[1282,1370,2009,2035]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="14.[151,269,1791,1815]" captionTargetBox="[171,1396,188,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[171,1415,103,1863]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19: Genitalia of Decidia spp. [scale = 1 mm]. 11. D. blapoides (Redtenbacher, 1906), 3 (MNHN), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 12. D. blapoides (Redtenbacher, 1906), Ƥ HT (MNCN), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 13. D. doylei (Caudell, 1906), 3 (MNCN), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 14. D. doylei (Caudell, 1906), Ƥ (MNCN), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 15. D. magnifica n. sp., 3 HT (MEFLG), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 16. D. magnifica n. sp., Ƥ PT (MEFLG), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 17. D. soranus (Westwood, 1859), 3 (ANSP), apex of abdomen (lateral view). 18. D. magnifica n. sp., 3 HT (MEFLG), left cercus (caudal view). 19. D. doylei (Caudell, 1906), 3 (MNCN), anal segment and cerci (caudal view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/187444/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[1337,1370,2009,2035]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
